AFRICAN SWINE FEVER - EUROPE (03): ITALY (PIEDMONT) WILD BOAR, OIE
******************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 7 Jan 2022
Source: OIE-WAHIS (World Animal Health Information System) 2022 [edited]
https://wahis.oie.int/#/report-info?reportId=46127


African swine fever virus (inf. with), Italy
----------------------------------------------
General information
Report type: immediate notification
Started on: 5 Jan 2022
Confirmed on: 7 Jan 2022
Reported on: 7 Jan 2022
Reason for notification: new strain in a zone or a compartment
Causal agent: African swine fever virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks (1)
Outbreak location: Ovada, Alessandria, Piemonte [Piedmont]
Date of start of the outbreak: 5 Jan 2022
Epidemiological unit: forest
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Wild boar (_Sus scrofa_): Suidae-Artiodactyla / - / 1 / 1 / - / - / 0

Affected population: The positivity was found on an animal found dead.

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments: Following the finding of a dead wild boar in northern Italy, the positivity for genotype 2 is reported, the same strain currently circulating in Europe, that characterizes the epidemic wave that began in 2007.

Control measures applied in domestic: surveillance within containment and/or the protection zone; surveillance outside containment and/or the protection zone; official destruction of animal products; ante- and post-mortem inspections; disinfection; stamping out; screening; official disposal of carcasses, by-products, and waste; movement control inside the country; zoning; traceability

Control measures applied in wild: screening; official disposal of carcasses, by-products, and waste; official destruction of animal products; movement control inside the country; ante- and post-mortem inspections; surveillance outside containment and/or the protection zone; surveillance within containment and/or the protection zone; zoning

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National Reference Laboratory for classical and African swine fever (national laboratory) / wild boar / real-time polymerase chain reaction (real-time PCR) / 7 Jan 2022 / positive

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED

[This official report complements the information published in ProMED posting 20220110.8700778. This is the 1st reported case of African swine fever [ASF] on Italy's mainland.

A comprehensive media report dated 10 Jan 2022 from Sassari (Sardinia, Italy), kindly forwarded by Sabine Zentis, provides additional information, including the following (in Italian, Google translated) statement: "As regards the cases discovered between the provinces of Alessandria (2 in Ovada) and that of Genoa, they are caused by ASFV genotype 2, which is different and more aggressive for wild boars than the ASFV genotype 1 [which has been circulating in Sardinia since decades]." (https://www.lanuovasardegna.it/regione/2022/01/09/news/peste-suina-tre-casi-nel-nord-italia-coldiretti-stop-embargo-per-l-isola-1.41110777)
- Mods CRD/AS

ProMED map of Alessandria, Piedmont, Italy: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=8700787,48165]
